From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Namecoin Integration <namecoin@example.org>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 0016] Phase 5: Three-stage enablement gating (Nightly -> Beta -> Release)

Implement Mozilla's standard graduation path for Namecoin (.bit) support:

  Stage A (Nightly):  about:config only, pref hidden from normal UI.
  Stage B (Beta):     Visible Settings toggle in Privacy & Security, default-off.
  Stage C (Release):  Default-off but toggle present; default-on only by
                      explicit future decision.

Changes:
  1. Add network.namecoin.settings_visible pref (StaticPrefList.yaml).
  2. New NamecoinFeature.sys.mjs — JS feature gate module that determines
     active stage and guards enablement by channel.
  3. Gate the Namecoin section in privacy.js behind settings_visible so
     it only appears when Stage B is shipped (Normandy/pref flip).
  4. Add Telemetry Scalars probe for tracking enablement state changes.

Bug: XXXXXX — [namecoin] Phase 5: Three-stage enablement gating
